---
// Footer.astro — Site footer
---

<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="footer-logo">Byzantine Doors</div>
  <div class="footer-text">
    Catechetical and parish resources for the Byzantine Christian tradition
  </div>
  <div class="footer-disclaimer">
    Byzantine Doors is an independent educational project created by a layperson to help English-speaking seekers and families discover the Byzantine Christian tradition. Theological content draws primarily from <em>Christ Our Pascha</em>, the catechism of the Ukrainian Greek-Catholic Church. English hymn texts are sourced from publicly available translations and may differ from those used in your parish. This site is not an official publication of any eparchy, diocese, or church body. For authoritative guidance on liturgical practice, fasting, and prayer, please consult your pastor.
  </div>
  <div class="footer-links">
    <a href="#">About</a>
    <a href="#">Contact</a>
    <a href="#">Sources</a>
    <a href="#">Privacy</a>
  </div>
</footer>

<style>
  .site-footer {
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--gold-10);
    padding: 48px 0 40px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .footer-logo {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--halo-gold);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .footer-text {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--deep-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .footer-disclaimer {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--deep-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 20px auto 0;
    padding: 0 40px;
  }
  .footer-disclaimer em {
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
  }
  .footer-links {
    margin-top: 16px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .footer-links a {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .footer-links a:hover {
    color: var(--beeswax);
  }
</style>
